subtasks: Gather supplies (seed trays, seed starting mix, grow lights)
Plant tomato seeds (fill trays, moisten mix, plant 1/4 inch deep)
Provide tomato seedlings with bright light (south-facing window or grow lights)
Gradually acclimate tomato seedlings to outdoor conditions
Plant pepper seeds (same steps as tomatoes)
Ensure peppers receive at least 14-16 hours of light
Gently brush seedlings to develop sturdier stems
Plant eggplant seeds (same steps as tomatoes and peppers)
Broccoli seedlings: prefer cooler temperature (60-65°F, moist but well-draining soil)
Cauliflower seedlings: same steps as broccoli
Start lettuce seeds (1/4 inch deep, cool temperatures)
Spinach seeds (1/2 inch deep, cool temperatures)
